  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anemia prevalence in orthopedic surgery is up to 30 %. Identifying those patients prior to
      surgery and treating them would be ideal. Different ways of determining hemoglobin Levels are
      available. In this study classical laboratory determination, determination with HemoCue® and
      Rad-67™ will be performed to compare precision of those three methods as well as their
      correlation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
